l'll go look in here.

502
00:27:00,560 --> 00:27:02,255
l'll check the kitchen.

503
00:27:07,267 --> 00:27:09,861
Are you in the kitchen? Dad?

504
00:27:13,640 --> 00:27:15,767
l'm worried. Do you think he's okay?

505
00:27:20,713 --> 00:27:22,977
-Who is it?
-lt's us, Dad!

506
00:27:30,390 --> 00:27:31,755
Who is that woman?

507
00:27:31,958 --> 00:27:33,448
lt's cool.

508
00:27:35,495 --> 00:27:36,860
lt's my girls!

509
00:27:37,063 --> 00:27:38,394
Hi, Daddy.

510
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:43,125
Georgie-Porgie! Evie-baby!

511
00:27:43,736 --> 00:27:45,601
-And Maddy!
-Hi, Daddy.

512
00:27:47,006 --> 00:27:49,133
-Are you okay?
-l'm fine. l'm great now!

513
00:27:49,342 --> 00:27:50,366
Come on in.

514
00:27:50,577 --> 00:27:52,545
Esther, say hello to the girls!

515
00:27:55,582 --> 00:27:57,209
You remember her, don't you?

516
00:27:59,485 --> 00:28:00,850
''Mouthwash''?

517
00:28:01,754 --> 00:28:03,085
''Rinse and spit''?

518
00:28:04,757 --> 00:28:06,281
-What does that mean?
-Esther.

519
00:28:06,492 --> 00:28:07,686
You're kidding!

520
00:28:07,927 --> 00:28:10,657
-lt's Esther.
-No way. Are you serious?

521
00:28:10,863 --> 00:28:12,592
Yeah, from the dentist.

522
00:28:13,967 --> 00:28:15,867
We remember you, sure.

523
00:28:16,302 --> 00:28:19,362
l bumped into your dad while visiting
my brother-in-law.

524
00:28:19,606 --> 00:28:23,042
He had to have his colon taken out.
Poor thing. My God!

525
00:28:23,276 --> 00:28:26,143
They're gonna connect
the whole thing back up again.

526
00:28:26,346 --> 00:28:30,840
So l was poking around in different
rooms looking for him, and here he was!

527
00:28:31,484 --> 00:28:32,815
He's cute!

528
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:35,883
Girls, let's go sit with the bullet.

529
00:28:41,561 --> 00:28:46,464
Well, now, l'm just gonna buzz off
and let you all catch up.

530
00:28:48,301 --> 00:28:50,030
And you....

531
00:28:51,304 --> 00:28:53,204
You know where to find me!

532
00:28:53,406 --> 00:28:54,566
Look at him.

533
00:28:57,744 --> 00:28:59,075
She's a great lay.

534
00:28:59,312 --> 00:29:00,643
Dad!

535
00:29:01,714 --> 00:29:06,549
l'm so sorry to hear about your mom.
l feel terrible about that.

536
00:29:06,986 --> 00:29:09,454
But if that happened to somebody
in my family...

537
00:29:09,656 --> 00:29:11,453
...l would stick to cars.

538
00:29:13,493 --> 00:29:14,960
What happened to Mom?

539
00:29:15,161 --> 00:29:17,994
l said she went down
in that crash in Denver.

540
00:29:18,498 --> 00:29:19,931
What crash in Denver?

541
00:29:20,400 --> 00:29:24,530
l'm telling you, people always think
that they remember plane crashes...

542
00:29:24,737 --> 00:29:26,602
...even though they never took place.

543
00:29:27,940 --> 00:29:29,134
But Mom's not dead.

544
00:29:29,342 --> 00:29:31,833
She's in Big Bear.
lt's the same thing.

545
00:29:34,614 --> 00:29:37,208
Guess you're feeling better, huh, Dad?

546
00:30:55,928 --> 00:30:57,623
l miss her, Evie.

547
00:31:00,633 --> 00:31:01,827
Mom?

548
00:31:03,102 --> 00:31:05,400
l can't sleep without her.

549
00:31:05,638 --> 00:31:09,039
l miss her just being there
and just....

550
00:31:10,276 --> 00:31:13,575
She's sort of....
She's the other half of me.

551
00:31:13,780 --> 00:31:16,681
l mean, l feel like a guy
with one leg.

552
00:31:18,651 --> 00:31:21,279
Yeah, l can't sleep without her.

553
00:32:46,405 --> 00:32:47,929
Hey, Mom.

554
00:32:48,774 --> 00:32:50,264
Are you taller?

555
00:32:52,411 --> 00:32:53,537
l don't think so.

556
00:32:55,381 --> 00:32:57,246
You're prettier than l remember.

557
00:33:00,419 --> 00:33:02,785
Mom, l wanted to ask you
about the roses.

558
00:33:02,989 --> 00:33:07,221
Are you supposed to cut them back to
a three-leaf configuration or a five?

559
00:33:09,328 --> 00:33:11,091
Get some cups here.

560
00:33:11,664 --> 00:33:13,291
ln the cabinet.

561
00:33:15,801 --> 00:33:18,770
-ls it locked?
-No, it's open. Right there.

562
00:33:19,505 --> 00:33:21,905
Lemon? Milk with your tea?

563
00:33:22,108 --> 00:33:24,076
l don't care.

564
00:33:24,477 --> 00:33:26,240
Lemon's better for you.

565
00:33:26,913 --> 00:33:27,937
Lemon?

566
00:33:38,357 --> 00:33:43,158
The roses are all leggy and sad.
Dad's not that much of a gardener.

567
00:33:43,529 --> 00:33:46,327
lt's a five-leaf configuration,
by the way.

568
00:33:54,040 --> 00:33:58,943
Mom, just come home. You have to,
because everything is a mess.

569
00:33:59,278 --> 00:34:02,145
Eve, dear, this is my home.

570
00:34:03,816 --> 00:34:06,182
What are you talking about?
This is nowhere.

571
00:34:06,652 --> 00:34:10,053
This is like you're living
with a bunch of squirrels.

572
00:34:10,289 --> 00:34:13,690
Come home and visit, and
just come and talk to Dad.

573
00:34:13,893 --> 00:34:16,293
You know, he tried to kill himself.

574
00:34:16,996 --> 00:34:18,759
But he didn't succeed.

575
00:34:19,832 --> 00:34:22,630
No, he took an overdose
of Percodan, Mom.

576
00:34:23,703 --> 00:34:24,727
Your father.

577
00:34:27,506 --> 00:34:30,441
Well, look, l'm very worried
about Maddy.

578
00:34:30,810 --> 00:34:34,405
She's dropped out.
She's living at the beach.

579
00:34:34,647 --> 00:34:38,413
She thinks she'll be a rock star,
and she can't carry a tune.

580
00:34:38,651 --> 00:34:40,642
Let me think how to put this.

581
00:34:41,687 --> 00:34:45,384
Motherhood doesn't turn out
to be a reason.

582
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:48,920
For what?

583
00:34:50,229 --> 00:34:54,996
What l mean is, l'm not one of those
women who needed to be a mother.

584
00:34:55,568 --> 00:34:59,971
When l was growing up, all the girls
wanted to be, so l thought l did too.

585
00:35:00,172 --> 00:35:02,003
But it didn't take.

586
00:35:06,412 --> 00:35:08,004
Just being honest.

587
00:35:11,083 --> 00:35:12,072
Well....

588
00:35:16,756 --> 00:35:17,848
Thank you.

589
00:35:56,262 --> 00:35:57,388
Dad!

590
00:35:58,664 --> 00:36:01,155
You need anything?
You want something?

591
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:03,960
-Yeah, drive me around.
-Are you all right?

592
00:36:04,170 --> 00:36:07,333
What's wrong?
Did you take some more pills?

593
00:36:07,573 --> 00:36:11,976
No, l just had a little scotch.
No pills.

594
00:36:12,244 --> 00:36:14,678
l was just kidding around
with the pills.

595
00:36:14,914 --> 00:36:15,846
Kidding around?

596
00:36:16,082 --> 00:36:17,743
l didn't mean to take them.

597
00:36:18,951 --> 00:36:20,179
Baby?

598
00:36:21,020 --> 00:36:22,510
Drive me.

599
00:36:23,589 --> 00:36:26,683
Well-- Yeah, okay. Whatever.

600
00:36:26,959 --> 00:36:28,893
Where do you wanna go?

601
00:36:32,098 --> 00:36:33,224
Home.

602
00:36:36,936 --> 00:36:38,460
Do you wanna get a tree?

603
00:36:39,605 --> 00:36:40,572
Yes!

604
00:36:40,773 --> 00:36:42,673
Do you wanna get a Christmas tree?

605
00:36:46,345 --> 00:36:47,972
Merry Christmas!

606
00:36:51,183 --> 00:36:53,617
Hey, Dad! Fake snow!

607
00:36:53,819 --> 00:36:56,982
Of course it's fake.
What do you want in L.A.? Real?

608
00:36:57,189 --> 00:37:00,852
We'll get a big one.
A big one, like always!

609
00:37:01,127 --> 00:37:05,223
Dad! How about this one?
Look at this. This is good!

610
00:37:05,464 --> 00:37:09,059
Bigger! That's a dwarf! lt's a runt!

611
00:37:09,368 --> 00:37:12,997
We'll get the King Kong of trees!

612
00:37:23,682 --> 00:37:26,082
-Look! What about this one?
-This one?

613
00:37:26,385 --> 00:37:29,980
Your mom always said,
''Don't get a big tree.''

614
00:37:30,189 --> 00:37:32,817
-Well, the hell with her!
-Yeah, to hell with her.

615
00:37:33,025 --> 00:37:35,721
Attagirl! That's my cookie!

616
00:37:36,128 --> 00:37:38,096
To hell with her!

617
00:37:38,330 --> 00:37:42,164
lt's snowing, Evie. lt's gonna
be a white Christmas.

618
00:37:44,837 --> 00:37:46,702
Look how beautiful it is!

619
00:37:46,906 --> 00:37:49,500
Oh, thank you, thank you!

620
00:37:49,708 --> 00:37:52,677
Beautiful snow! Thank you!

621
00:38:01,187 --> 00:38:02,381
He's dead.

622
00:38:05,057 --> 00:38:06,217
Hello?

623
00:38:07,393 --> 00:38:09,520
Mom, the door!

624
00:38:11,530 --> 00:38:13,657
Eve, it's Maddy. Open up!

625
00:38:18,704 --> 00:38:20,729
Oh, look at that! Oh, good!

626
00:38:20,973 --> 00:38:23,464
Hey, he loves you. That's so good!

627
00:38:23,709 --> 00:38:25,677
Eve, meet Buck.

628
00:38:25,878 --> 00:38:28,870
-This is Buck?
-Yeah, isn't he awesome? l know.

629
00:38:29,114 --> 00:38:31,548
Wanna hear the saddest?
He's got Lyme disease.

630
00:38:31,917 --> 00:38:35,683
Probably from all those moose in
Montana. l just got the results.

631
00:38:36,589 --> 00:38:37,920
Where are you going?

632
00:38:38,123 --> 00:38:40,023
-Wait! Where is he going?
-lt's okay.

633
00:38:40,226 --> 00:38:41,716
Hey there, doggy! Whoa!

634
00:38:41,927 --> 00:38:44,896
Look at him! He's going to eat
the couch. Get him off!

635
00:38:45,097 --> 00:38:47,531
He would never do that.
He's an angel.

636
00:38:47,733 --> 00:38:49,496
He gets these paralyzed attacks.

637
00:38:49,735 --> 00:38:53,193
He has to have four pills a day,
and l'm on the set all day.

638
00:38:53,405 --> 00:38:55,839
Just forget it, Maddy.
l'm not doing that.

639
00:38:56,508 --> 00:38:57,736
He won't survive!

640
00:38:58,077 --> 00:38:59,305
That better be Georgia.

641
00:38:59,511 --> 00:39:02,810
l've been trying to reach her,
and she never calls me back!

642
00:39:05,751 --> 00:39:08,413
Georgia. Hi. Listen.

643
00:39:08,621 --> 00:39:11,454
This speech, you've got
to do it for me.

644
00:39:11,657 --> 00:39:15,650
You've got to come here and do it
on April 7th. One week.

645
00:39:16,195 --> 00:39:17,457
Well, fine.

646
00:39:17,930 --> 00:39:20,831
-Fine?
-When have l everletyou down?

647
00:39:22,268 --> 00:39:23,235
Thank you.

648
00:39:24,436 --> 00:39:25,334
That's old.

649
00:39:25,638 --> 00:39:27,071
Yeah, Maddy's here.

650
00:39:27,273 --> 00:39:30,106
What? Why is she there so early?

651
00:39:30,776 --> 00:39:31,970
l see. Silence.

652
00:39:32,177 --> 00:39:34,168
Tell me later.
l can't wait.

653
00:39:34,380 --> 00:39:35,347
How's Dad?

654
00:39:35,547 --> 00:39:38,948
l spend my life at that hospital,
and he will die asking for you.

655
00:39:39,151 --> 00:39:40,948
Excuse me. Excuse me.

656
00:39:42,054 --> 00:39:46,388
Our father is not dying. lt's
possible our father is never dying.

657
00:39:46,625 --> 00:39:51,187
You need more in your life, so you
don't blow things out of proportion.

658
00:39:51,497 --> 00:39:55,365
You are such a hysteric when it comes
to Dad. You've got to get a grip.

659
00:39:55,634 --> 00:39:57,397
One more thing before l go.

660
00:39:57,636 --> 00:40:01,868
You know what? l'll send you my
banner. l'm using it for my speeches.

661
00:40:03,409 --> 00:40:04,706
Your banner?

662
00:40:04,910 --> 00:40:06,275
She has a banner!

663
00:40:07,313 --> 00:40:08,746
What does it say? ''Georgia''?

664
00:40:08,948 --> 00:40:11,178
l'll be in L.A.--
That's enough. Thank you.

665
00:40:11,383 --> 00:40:14,375
Jonathan. l've got it now.
My hair looks really good.

666
00:40:14,586 --> 00:40:17,555
Jesus Christ, he's gotta--
Take a vacation, will you?

667
00:40:17,957 --> 00:40:21,916
l've got this L.A. advertising push, so
l can knock off your little thing too.

668
00:40:22,494 --> 00:40:24,553
l was gonna wiggle out ofit.

669
00:40:24,863 --> 00:40:26,660
Don't wiggle out on me!

670
00:40:29,335 --> 00:40:31,235
When are you coming to the hospital?

671
00:40:31,837 --> 00:40:34,829
Jesse, come in here!
lt's breakfast time!

672
00:40:35,040 --> 00:40:36,735
Or are you just too busy?

673
00:40:37,009 --> 00:40:39,307
Take it easy! My God, you're so edgy.

674
00:40:39,845 --> 00:40:42,678
l'm coming to the hospital
this week at lunch.

675
00:40:43,015 --> 00:40:46,917
l'm coming with my leg in a cast.
Juliana got hit by an Aston Martin.

676
00:40:49,121 --> 00:40:49,951
Fine.

677
00:40:54,560 --> 00:40:56,084
Buck, honey.

678
00:40:56,295 --> 00:41:00,994
Mommy has to leave you with Aunt Eve
because you have to have your pills.

679
00:41:01,200 --> 00:41:02,565
Baby.

680
00:41:02,968 --> 00:41:07,632
Okay, she's a very nice person.
Yeah. There she is.

681
00:41:09,875 --> 00:41:12,002
Georgia's doing you a favor.

682
00:41:15,481 --> 00:41:19,042
Don't cut it down.
Just put it up behind the dais.

683
00:41:19,251 --> 00:41:22,311
Yes. Just stick--
lt doesn't matter.

684
00:41:22,554 --> 00:41:24,488
You can't cut it down.

685
00:41:24,757 --> 00:41:27,453
No, l'll be there in exactly--

686
00:41:39,738 --> 00:41:41,672
Come on. Just--
All right. Come on!

687
00:41:41,907 --> 00:41:44,671
Come on, Buck, swallow this!

688
00:41:46,078 --> 00:41:49,946
Come on. Now, you want this pill.
You need it!

689
00:41:52,818 --> 00:41:57,118
Juliana. As l feared,
you have a shattered fibula.

690
00:41:57,356 --> 00:41:59,415
How can you tell he's gay? He is gay.

691
00:41:59,625 --> 00:42:00,614
He's not convincing.

692
00:42:00,826 --> 00:42:03,818
Name one actor on TV playing
a heterosexual that isn't gay.

693
00:42:04,263 --> 00:42:06,128
Walter Cronkite.

694
00:42:09,268 --> 00:42:12,328
Hey, your dad's on the machine.

695
00:42:13,272 --> 00:42:14,603
Look what l built.

696
00:42:14,973 --> 00:42:17,032
ls that actress Doris Day?

697
00:42:17,276 --> 00:42:21,178
Go sit in your special chair.
Back there. Yeah, there you go.

698
00:42:21,447 --> 00:42:22,778
You're in love with him?

699
00:42:24,149 --> 00:42:28,313
How can you be in love with him?
He looks like some sort of a beetle.

700
00:42:29,955 --> 00:42:31,752
He doesn't look like a beetle!

701
00:42:31,957 --> 00:42:34,949
But why can't you just enjoy
something that l'm in?

702
00:42:35,160 --> 00:42:36,718
l was once arrested.

703
00:42:37,863 --> 00:42:40,627
l was in isolation.

704
00:42:41,667 --> 00:42:45,125
As part of the punishment,
they showed your show.

705
00:42:48,373 --> 00:42:50,204
l'll get you so good!

706
00:42:54,346 --> 00:42:55,643
Just eat one!

707
00:42:57,716 --> 00:42:58,808
God!

708
00:43:14,266 --> 00:43:18,828
Well, tell Maddy to get herass over
to the house and pick up the dog.

709
00:43:19,037 --> 00:43:20,698
What are we? A kennel?

710
00:43:20,906 --> 00:43:24,171
l swear, Joe, it's like feeding
a pill to a whale.

711
00:43:24,676 --> 00:43:27,110
Honey, this is how
this stuffhappens, okay?

712
00:43:27,346 --> 00:43:30,782
You have to stop letting people
walk all overyou.

713
00:43:31,016 --> 00:43:34,474
You are a million miles away
in some stupid town...

714
00:43:34,686 --> 00:43:37,177
...talking to people
who mean nothing to you.

715
00:43:37,389 --> 00:43:40,324
Don't call and give me orders.
You are not on my side.

716
00:43:40,526 --> 00:43:41,754
You cannot mean that.

717
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:46,727
l don't know what l mean, all right?
Don't tell me l do, because l don't!

718
00:43:48,133 --> 00:43:50,363
l don't want to talk right now, Joe!

719
00:43:50,569 --> 00:43:51,763
lt's Dr. Kelly.

720
00:43:54,473 --> 00:43:55,531
What is it?

721
00:43:55,874 --> 00:43:57,364
Well....

722
00:43:58,043 --> 00:43:59,840
Your father is missing.

723
00:44:00,045 --> 00:44:01,410
Missing?

724
00:44:02,548 --> 00:44:04,379
Well, that's impossible.

725
00:44:04,883 --> 00:44:09,752
He can't walk. He's in a locked ward.
l mean, he must be misplaced.

726
00:44:09,955 --> 00:44:11,013
Nevertheless....

727
00:44:11,223 --> 00:44:14,624
Did you check the other rooms?
Did you check the female patients?

728
00:44:14,826 --> 00:44:17,818
Check in the bed of every single
female patient.

729
00:44:18,063 --> 00:44:20,793
You should talk to that nurse
with the curly hair.

730
00:44:20,999 --> 00:44:24,059
Did you talk to Angie
from the Motion Picture Home?

731
00:44:24,269 --> 00:44:26,794
l'm sure we'll turn him up.
Sit tight.

732
00:44:27,005 --> 00:44:28,404
What am l supposed--?

733
00:44:57,436 --> 00:44:58,835
Come on, Daddy!

734
00:45:34,940 --> 00:45:36,339
We got a call from Angelo Drive.

735
00:45:36,541 --> 00:45:38,839
Found. Found.

736
00:45:50,822 --> 00:45:53,188
-ls he right in there?
-Yeah, sure, go on in.

737
00:45:53,392 --> 00:45:55,019
Thank you. l'm very sorry.

738
00:45:55,227 --> 00:45:56,489
That's okay.

739
00:46:15,447 --> 00:46:18,348
-lt's my Evie!
-Hi, Dad.

740
00:46:19,051 --> 00:46:21,019
Come over here, Evie.

741
00:46:22,087 --> 00:46:26,956
l can't get up. l got myself in here,
and now l can't get up.

742
00:46:29,294 --> 00:46:30,556
How did you get here?

743
00:46:30,762 --> 00:46:33,629
Taxi. Best way to travel.
Don't forget that.

744
00:46:34,099 --> 00:46:36,260
All right. l'll try not to.

745
00:46:36,601 --> 00:46:39,001
What's that over there?

746
00:46:39,905 --> 00:46:42,806
lt looks like some ginger
in a large vase.

747
00:46:43,041 --> 00:46:45,305
Maybe they like that kind of thing.

748
00:46:45,610 --> 00:46:46,736
Who?

749
00:46:48,213 --> 00:46:50,477
The people that live in our house now.

750
00:46:56,221 --> 00:47:00,055
You know, sometimes l don't
recognize my own hands.

751
