01:16:43,273 --> 01:16:46,470
Which is another reason
she didn't bother to come.

1245
01:16:46,676 --> 01:16:50,271
l've told you a million times. Stop
talking to me as if l'm like you!

1246
01:16:50,480 --> 01:16:51,674
Oh, fuck you!

1247
01:16:51,915 --> 01:16:52,904
And fuck you!

1248
01:16:53,416 --> 01:16:55,384
-Excuse me.
-What? Oh, God!

1249
01:16:55,585 --> 01:16:57,314
You have a phone call.

1250
01:17:09,466 --> 01:17:12,094
Did Mitchell know to any degree
what was going on?

1251
01:17:12,302 --> 01:17:13,132
Who is this?

1252
01:17:13,336 --> 01:17:17,204
That's the President's smoking-gun
call with Haldeman. Talk on this.

1253
01:17:21,811 --> 01:17:23,574
Yes, this is Eve Marks.

1254
01:17:29,819 --> 01:17:31,081
Oh, my God.

1255
01:17:34,024 --> 01:17:35,855
-What happened?
-He's in a coma.

1256
01:17:36,059 --> 01:17:37,356
l'm going to the hospital.

1257
01:17:37,561 --> 01:17:39,188
So am l.

1258
01:17:40,330 --> 01:17:41,820
So am l!

1259
01:18:24,307 --> 01:18:28,038
Wait! Wait for me.
What's the big rush, you guys?

1260
01:18:32,716 --> 01:18:33,683
Hello, what?

1261
01:18:35,785 --> 01:18:39,243
No, l can't right now, all right?
l'll talk to you later.

1262
01:18:43,159 --> 01:18:44,319
lt's here.

1263
01:18:45,795 --> 01:18:46,819
Oh, my God.

1264
01:18:55,905 --> 01:18:57,065
Dad?

1265
01:19:07,951 --> 01:19:09,145
Dad?

1266
01:19:10,587 --> 01:19:13,021
-Can he hear us?
-Why does he have one pillow?

1267
01:19:13,523 --> 01:19:16,754
A person can't possibly be
comfortable with one-- What?

1268
01:19:17,427 --> 01:19:18,416
What?

1269
01:19:19,629 --> 01:19:23,622
Are you not going to speak to me?
ls that what this is about?

1270
01:19:23,967 --> 01:19:26,595
Why aren't you talking to me?
l didn't do anything.

1271
01:19:26,803 --> 01:19:28,794
l see. And l did. ls that it?

1272
01:19:29,639 --> 01:19:31,937
This is just--
This is really great.

1273
01:19:32,709 --> 01:19:34,301
This is really great.

1274
01:19:39,649 --> 01:19:42,618
Can you believe she's
making this about herself?

1275
01:19:46,222 --> 01:19:47,314
Fine.

1276
01:19:47,791 --> 01:19:49,622
Don't talk to me. Good.

1277
01:20:59,562 --> 01:21:01,530
Do l have anything in my teeth?

1278
01:21:10,440 --> 01:21:13,375
You're not the only one
that this is happening to.

1279
01:21:15,311 --> 01:21:16,471
l know.

1280
01:21:17,213 --> 01:21:18,544
Sorry.

1281
01:21:21,217 --> 01:21:24,983
But since l'm an actress,
l suppose l could use this stuff.

1282
01:21:25,221 --> 01:21:27,052
That's the good part, right?

1283
01:21:27,957 --> 01:21:30,391
The sad part is that
l really love Dad.

1284
01:21:34,397 --> 01:21:35,887
l'm his baby.

1285
01:21:38,601 --> 01:21:41,161
Do you want a candy bar?
l'm getting a candy bar.

1286
01:21:46,376 --> 01:21:51,245
Excuse me. Aren't you
Juliana on Living Dangerously?.

1287
01:21:51,748 --> 01:21:53,045
Yes. Yes, l am.

1288
01:21:53,249 --> 01:21:55,843
You should have never
gone to the Bahamas...

1289
01:21:56,085 --> 01:21:57,746
...because he cheated on you.

1290
01:21:57,954 --> 01:21:59,080
Thanks.

1291
01:22:00,089 --> 01:22:02,182
She recognized me!

1292
01:22:05,962 --> 01:22:08,089
Georgia, someone just recognized me!

1293
01:22:08,932 --> 01:22:10,297
Great.

1294
01:22:30,119 --> 01:22:31,313
Thank you.

1295
01:22:34,624 --> 01:22:36,717
All right, look.
l know what you said.

1296
01:22:36,960 --> 01:22:38,860
-About what?
-That l wanted it.

1297
01:22:39,062 --> 01:22:41,860
Forget it.
l'm sorry l said that, Eve.

1298
01:22:44,067 --> 01:22:47,332
There are things that happen
that you just don't choose.

1299
01:22:47,537 --> 01:22:48,868
You know, they just....

1300
01:22:49,405 --> 01:22:52,135
You embrace them, and they become
part of your identity.

1301
01:22:52,342 --> 01:22:55,573
And Mom left Dad to me. Or at least--
l don't know.

1302
01:22:55,812 --> 01:22:59,213
lt felt like she did.
And part of me was so...

1303
01:23:00,683 --> 01:23:02,207
...proud.

1304
01:23:03,052 --> 01:23:06,681
Then the other part of me just
resented every second of it...

1305
01:23:06,890 --> 01:23:09,859
...because he is just a handful.

1306
01:23:10,827 --> 01:23:14,729
l should have been here. l should've
been here, and l know that.

1307
01:23:14,931 --> 01:23:17,695
But l knew that if you were here,
he didn't need me.

1308
01:23:17,901 --> 01:23:19,493
l mean, let's face it.

1309
01:23:20,770 --> 01:23:22,897
God help anyone who needs me.

1310
01:23:26,075 --> 01:23:27,906
l needed you.

1311
01:23:29,412 --> 01:23:32,210
He didn't need you. l needed you.

1312
01:23:33,016 --> 01:23:34,415
l'm sorry.

1313
01:23:36,452 --> 01:23:38,181
l'm very sorry, all right?

1314
01:23:38,922 --> 01:23:41,356
-l'm really sorry.
-l'm sorry too.

1315
01:23:43,026 --> 01:23:46,518
l love you very much.
Do you know that?

1316
01:23:47,230 --> 01:23:48,754
l love you, and....

1317
01:23:49,165 --> 01:23:50,792
l gave you that great speech.

1318
01:23:51,034 --> 01:23:52,865
Yes, yes, you did.

1319
01:23:53,603 --> 01:23:54,865
And l'm very grateful.

1320
01:23:55,071 --> 01:23:57,801
Okay, you're grateful. Shut up.

1321
01:23:59,876 --> 01:24:01,366
You know, Eve...

1322
01:24:03,046 --> 01:24:06,880
...l have never been jealous of anyone
in my entire life, but...

1323
01:24:08,585 --> 01:24:10,280
...l have to admit that...

1324
01:24:12,221 --> 01:24:15,122
...l am just the tiniest bit
jealous of your heart.

1325
01:24:24,734 --> 01:24:26,725
-You forgive me?
-l love you. l do.

1326
01:24:26,936 --> 01:24:28,460
l love you.

1327
01:24:34,243 --> 01:24:35,471
Who does Dad look like?

1328
01:24:35,678 --> 01:24:38,408
Now he looks like that senator.
What was his name?

1329
01:24:38,615 --> 01:24:41,379
The one who got insulted,
and his wife cried.

1330
01:24:41,584 --> 01:24:42,949
Edmund Muskie.

1331
01:24:43,152 --> 01:24:44,414
Yes!

1332
01:24:45,088 --> 01:24:46,385
Who was Edmund Muskie?

1333
01:24:46,589 --> 01:24:48,750
l've been trying
to remember the name...

1334
01:24:48,958 --> 01:24:53,418
...of this short, blond actress
from the '50s, or maybe it was the '40s.

1335
01:24:53,630 --> 01:24:55,996
-What about Vera-Ellen?
-No. Very thin hair.

1336
01:24:56,199 --> 01:24:57,325
Donna Reed.

1337
01:24:57,533 --> 01:25:00,593
-Janet Leigh.
-Donna Reed wasn't short or blond.

1338
01:25:00,803 --> 01:25:02,100
Doris Day. l'm right.

1339
01:25:02,305 --> 01:25:03,465
Cleo!

1340
01:25:06,109 --> 01:25:07,076
Who was she?

1341
01:25:07,276 --> 01:25:09,836
-Who was she?
-Daddy's favorite.

1342
01:25:10,113 --> 01:25:12,138
He picked her up in
an ltalian restaurant.

1343
01:25:12,348 --> 01:25:13,212
Wait a minute.

1344
01:25:13,449 --> 01:25:15,815
She played wimps,
and she was kind of wide.

1345
01:25:16,019 --> 01:25:17,646
Doris Day. Wide.

1346
01:25:17,987 --> 01:25:21,252
Please tell me and give me
peace of mind.

1347
01:25:23,159 --> 01:25:24,956
June Allyson.

1348
01:25:29,298 --> 01:25:30,458
Dad?

1349
01:25:30,667 --> 01:25:31,964
Oh, Daddy!

1350
01:25:33,636 --> 01:25:36,366
Did he talk? He said, ''June Allyson''!

1351
01:25:37,140 --> 01:25:39,631
Did you just say, ''June Allyson''?
Nurse!

1352
01:25:41,878 --> 01:25:44,847
He's coming around!
He just said, ''June Allyson.''

1353
01:25:45,048 --> 01:25:46,345
Check and see. lt's fine.

1354
01:25:46,549 --> 01:25:49,074
-Doesn't start with an ''L.''
-lt almost does.

1355
01:25:49,485 --> 01:25:51,510
Maddy, it almost starts with an ''L.''

1356
01:26:17,180 --> 01:26:18,442
Dad?

1357
01:26:28,691 --> 01:26:31,626
He said, ''June Allyson.'' He's dead.

1358
01:27:10,566 --> 01:27:12,898
Evie, John Waynejust called.

1359
01:27:13,102 --> 01:27:14,899
Tell Georgia! Tell Maddy!

1360
01:27:15,338 --> 01:27:19,297
Georgie-Porgie! Evie-baby!

1361
01:27:19,509 --> 01:27:24,344
l love all my beautiful,
beautiful girls.

1362
01:27:27,116 --> 01:27:28,981
lt's my Evie.

1363
01:27:29,619 --> 01:27:33,146
Look how beautiful you are
in the snow.

1364
01:27:35,024 --> 01:27:38,687
That's my Evie. That's my cookie.

1365
01:27:46,803 --> 01:27:49,772
Did you take--? You did.

1366
01:27:49,972 --> 01:27:51,837
You took every almond out of here.

1367
01:27:52,041 --> 01:27:53,599
Every single one.

1368
01:27:56,712 --> 01:27:57,838
What about the celery?

1369
01:27:58,047 --> 01:27:59,275
Did you listen to me?

1370
01:27:59,849 --> 01:28:01,373
Georgia, it looks exactly right.

1371
01:28:01,617 --> 01:28:04,279
Are these onions supposed
to get this limp?

1372
01:28:04,487 --> 01:28:06,887
Yes, they are. lt's called cooking.

1373
01:28:07,123 --> 01:28:10,320
That's what happens to an onion.
But wait. See?

1374
01:28:10,526 --> 01:28:14,223
That looks very good.
You have made my stuffing.

1375
01:28:15,164 --> 01:28:17,564
Let me see what this is like.
All right.

1376
01:28:20,236 --> 01:28:21,601
This is so good!

1377
01:28:21,804 --> 01:28:23,328
lt's so good!

1378
01:28:23,539 --> 01:28:26,702
l can't believe you guys are doing
this. l can't believe it.

1379
01:28:26,909 --> 01:28:29,434
-Does it need more apricots?
-lt doesn't need anything!

1380
01:28:29,645 --> 01:28:32,375
Please sit and have fun.
Enjoy your life.

1381
01:28:32,582 --> 01:28:36,518
We're supposed to put the stuffing
inside the bird with our hands?

1382
01:28:36,719 --> 01:28:39,620
You have to stuff it way
to the back of the bird.

1383
01:28:39,822 --> 01:28:42,120
lt'll be goopy and awful,
but you have to do it.

1384
01:28:42,325 --> 01:28:44,156
Well, you enjoy that.

1385
01:28:46,329 --> 01:28:48,092
That's my gift to you.

1386
01:28:48,331 --> 01:28:52,734
You guys, listen. l do want to tell
you that l've decided to quit acting.

1387
01:28:53,436 --> 01:28:56,633
My character gets killed
in some random violence...

1388
01:28:56,839 --> 01:28:58,898
...while drinking a decaf cappuccino.

1389
01:28:59,742 --> 01:29:01,437
That's so sad!

1390
01:29:02,078 --> 01:29:03,409
And so l quit.

1391
01:29:04,113 --> 01:29:06,308
l'm sad for you. This is sad.

1392
01:29:06,549 --> 01:29:07,675
This bird is done.

1393
01:29:07,884 --> 01:29:09,283
You were good.

1394
01:29:09,919 --> 01:29:12,251
You were great, l'm sure.
Please open the door.

1395
01:29:12,455 --> 01:29:14,184
ls the oven preheated?

1396
01:29:18,628 --> 01:29:21,529
-ls it heavy?
-Yes! Could you help me?

1397
01:29:21,731 --> 01:29:22,993
lt is really heavy.

1398
01:29:23,866 --> 01:29:25,959
You're strong. lt's in!

1399
01:29:26,669 --> 01:29:29,604
You did it! All right!

1400
01:29:31,607 --> 01:29:33,302
Let's go sit with the bullet!

1401
01:29:34,210 --> 01:29:36,041
Do you wanna sit with the bullet?

1402
01:29:36,312 --> 01:29:38,109
-Thanks for helping!
-You're welcome.

1403
01:29:38,314 --> 01:29:40,612
You know what?
You're a little bit shiny!

1404
01:29:41,550 --> 01:29:42,881
This is Donna Karan!

1405
01:29:43,085 --> 01:29:45,679
Good God! That's Donna Karan!

1406
01:29:46,322 --> 01:29:47,914
No, wait a minute!

1407
01:29:48,925 --> 01:29:50,825
You can't stop me!

1408
01:29:54,263 --> 01:29:56,424
lt's in your mouth.

1409
01:30:59,495 --> 01:31:02,396
No, Maddy. Eve, help me!

1410
01:31:11,574 --> 01:31:13,974
l have a Donna Karan dress....

1411
01:31:14,677 --> 01:31:16,042
Wait a minute!

